1. Add the `.DS_Store` pattern to your `.gitignore` file (which you already did):
    ```ignore
    **/.DS_Store
    ```
**/.DS_Store
2. Remove the `.DS_Store` files from the repository's index:
    ```sh
    find . -name .DS_Store -print0 | xargs -0 git rm --cached
    ```

3. Commit the changes:
    ```sh
    git commit -m "Remove .DS_Store files from repository"
    ```

4. Push the changes to the remote repository:
    ```sh
    git push
    ```

This will remove the `.DS_Store` files from the repository and ensure they are ignored in future commits.